parameters: Cors the Wanderer: Huff...huff...please, hurry and run away!
Girl: But! My father and mother are!
Cors the Wanderer: This is no time for idle talk...!

Cors the Wanderer: I understand, surrender and while I'm
being eaten by this thing, please go and call for help.
Girl: B-But...then, what about the old man?!

Cors the Wanderer: You want to save your parents, right?
It's a big gamble, but if I can meet some women wielding
large swords...
Cors the Wanderer: We've won! Now, let's go!

Cors the Wanderer: Tch, is this a new move... If it comes to
this, then--

Thief Nora: Please don't break the promise you made with me
without permission!
Thief Nora: Now, it's our turn to be your opponents!

Priestess Sophia: The healing is complete. Please evacuate
to a safe place.
Girl's Father: Thank you so much, you're our savior!

Cors the Wanderer: Looks like I haven't run out of luck. For
now, I've kept my promise, so I guess it's time for me to--
Girl: Thank you, old man! You saved my mom and dad!
Girl: Thank you for saving me!
Thief Nora: Thank you for keeping your promise with me.

Cors the Wanderer: Wasn't I supposed to fight a dragon after
this?
Clea: Yes, I'm heading to the rooftop.
Cors the Wanderer: Is the prince coming there?

Cors the Wanderer: Well then, I'll come along too. I've come
this far, so if I'm lucky, I might receive a reward from the
new king...

Cors the Wanderer: Even if I have bad luck, I'll at least be
a shield for everyone.
